ce:section.ce:para:
In addition, because the diagnosis determined by a single indicator may not be accurate in practical application, it is often necessary to judge by other indicators at the same time, so we studied the ability to detect two different antigen types (NES and CEA) at different doses; Fig. 8
                        A shows the fluorescence recovery values of these antigen types. Then we compared the relationship between the calculated values of antigen theory (10, 20, 50, 100, 150 ng/mL) and the actual measured values. The slope of this linear fitting equation is greater than 0.96, which is close to 1, indicating that the detection results showed a good correlation between theoretical value and measured value. We found that the average recovery rate of NSE and CEA in normal serum was about 98 % by using the same formula Eq. (1.3) (Table 2
                        ), which proved that the developed probe is a reliable and practical analytical method for accurately measuring NSE and CEA.
